    • Method Detail

      • getRevision

        public Number getRevision()
        This method gets the number of the specific revision of the object referenced by this EntityId. If the associated object is NOT version controlled (e.g. a class or field), then the revision will always be null.
        Further a revision of null always points to the latest revision of an object.
        Returns:
        the revision or null for the latest revision.
        See Also:
        RevisionedEntity.getRevision(), RevisionedEntity.LATEST_REVISION

      • getTypeId

        public long getTypeId()
        This method gets the identifier representing the type of the referenced entity or object. The type is typically directly related to the Class reflecting the object. However, in dynamically or mixed typed object-worlds (often used in content-management-systems) two instances of the same java Class may be considered to have different types that can only be determined at runtime. To resolve an EntityId a central component is required that can map the EntityId.getTypeId() to the actual type (e.g. Class object) and vice versa.
        Returns:
        the classId.

      • getObjectId

        public long getObjectId()
        This method gets the unique identifier of an entity (or any other object).
        Returns:
        the object-id.
        See Also:
        GenericEntity.getId()
